<item>
            <title>[SEC-3010] Misleading error message when using wrong schema</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-3010</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I am using spring and spring security and got this error message:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;org.springframework.beans.factory.parsing.BeanDefinitionParsingException: Configuration problem: You cannot use a spring-security-2.0.xsd or spring-security-3.0.xsd or spring-security-3.1.xsd schema with Spring Security 3.2. Please update your schema declarations to the 3.2 schema&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I was using 3.2 schemas. The message got away when changing it to 4.0, same for spring framework.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Suggestion: change the message to something dynamic that doesn&apos;t need to be adjusted, e.g. &quot;you used XXXX.xsd but the current software version is YYY. Please update your schema declarations to the current schema.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Windows 7, Tomcat 8</environment>
